  "original_title": "\u0bb5\u0b9f\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0bae\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b9a\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0ba4\u0bc8 \u0b87\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bc1 \u0ba4\u0bc6\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0bae\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b9a\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bcd\u0baf \u0bae\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f \u0bb5\u0bc7\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbe\u0bae\u0bcd - \u0b8e\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Do not seek to do to the people of the South today what was done to the people of the North - Iran",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "The executive presidential system is the root cause of all problems.",
        "Don't try to do to the people of the south today what was done to the people of the north by using emergency law.",
        "United People's Shakti member Eran Wickramaratne told the House that the government should avoid misrepresenting the protest.",
        "He said the above while addressing the debate on the Emergency Act in Parliament on Wednesday (27).",
        "The government should refrain from misrepresenting the struggle going forward. There is no alternative that those who act against the law should be punished.",
        "The people are involved in the protest with different demands. The people involved in the protest are expecting system change (chishtam change). They also mention that Parliament should also be completely transformed.",
        "The Chief Whip of the ruling party said that it was wrong for the youth involved in the protest to bathe in the swimming pool at the Presidential Palace.",
        "If so, are things like extortion, soil digging, deforestation not a crime? On the other hand, the protestors are acting in an unethical manner, he said. All the people of the country are questioning the ethics of the members of parliament.",
        "Presidential system with executive power is the main factor behind all the problems. He said the government should remember that it should not try to do to the people of the South what it did to the people of the North by using the Emergency Act."
      ],
